1
00:00:00,100 --> 00:00:16,984
Compression is applied per batch: snappy (low C P U, good ratio), lz4 (fastest), gzip (best ratio, highest C P U), zstd (best ratio + speed balance, Kafka 2.1+).

2
00:00:16,934 --> 00:00:27,671
Compressed batches are written to disk and decompressed by the consumer — not by the broker — making this effectively free from the broker's perspective.

3
00:00:27,671 --> 00:00:31,921
Master this, and you're not just interview-ready.

4
00:00:31,921 --> 00:00:34,118
You're production-ready.

5
00:00:34,118 --> 00:00:35,868
That's rare.

